Old Value: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the study epoch, i.e., the named time period defined in the protocol, wherein a study activity is specified and unchanging throughout the interval, to support a study-specific purpose.
New Value: The literal identifier (i.e., distinctive designation) of the study epoch, i.e., the named time period defined in the protocol, wherein a study activity is specified and unchanging throughout the interval, to support a study-specific purpose.

Old Value: A characterization or classification of the study epoch, i.e., the named time period defined in the protocol, wherein a study activity is specified and unchanging throughout the interval, to support a study-specific purpose.
New Value: A characterization or classification of the study epoch, i.e., the named time period defined in the protocol, wherein a study activity is specified and unchanging throughout the interval, to support a study-specific purpose.

Old Value: A named time period defined in the protocol, wherein a study activity is specified and unchanging throughout the interval, to support a study-specific purpose.
New Value: A named time period defined in the protocol, wherein a study activity is specified and unchanging throughout the interval, to support a study-specific purpose.

Old Value: A characterization or classification of the study arm with respect to where the study arm data originates.
New Value: A characterization or classification of the study arm with respect to where the study arm data originates.

Old Value: A symbol or combination of symbols which is assigned to the members of a collection.
New Value: The literal value of a response code.

Old Value: The nature of the investigation for which study information is being collected. (After clinicaltrials.gov)
New Value: The nature of the investigation for which study information is being collected. (After clinicaltrials.gov)

Old Value: A representation of a particular edition or snapshot of the study definition document as it exists at a particular point in time.
New Value: A sequence of characters used to identify the version of the study definition document.

Old Value: A set of letters that are drawn from a word or from a sequence of words and that are used for brevity in place of the full word or phrase. (CDISC Glossary)
New Value: The literal value of an instance of unstructured text that is used as the abbreviation.
